column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Mostly Cloudy , Light Rain , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column14: Snowshoe frame mmt at bridge 1km u/s of station. Only 2nd time measuring here. It isn't a great section, very bouldery and fast flow, but with cableway condemned it is the only feasible alternative above wading depth. Many panels have very low 0.8 velocities due to the boulders, and 0.2/0.6/0.8 was used. Many times sounding would hit rock at e.g. 1.26 and then try again and hit at e.g. 1.90. With boulders, no issue of creating depression so sounded numerous times at each to try to get the most vertical and common depth.  HFC Comments: Control Condition: clear Measurement Section Condition: open Weather Condition: o/c Wind Velocity: 15 Wind Direction: d/s Reset applied to H1 logger at 10:48. Offset reading as -infinity leading to stage error. Fixed at 10:56. A few sticks are caught in o-line. Waded in at 11:15 to clear. Stepped on screwdriver when wading in. Re-leveled for later cut. column14: BM1 IS UNSTABLE. CORRECTED MGH 1.874 + 0.032 = 1.906. First attempt at snowshoe frame mmt from bridge 1km upstream. Very bouldery, and with weight swinging in the current it was difficult to determine sounding depth. Possible overestimates of depth due to angled line in sections of higher flow. Many 0.2/0.8 panels had low 0.8 velocities, so it is possible 0.6 panels may not represent average velocity well. Ideally would use more than 50lb weight, but couldn't with snowshoe frame. First mmt over wading depth since 2015. Might be too shallow but thought about trying Cablefox mmt. However, would need a tall step ladder to be able to remove cablecar safely.
